comments.content:
Agreed that it's a very nice site. I like his visual explanation of what happens when setting two spaces [between sentences](http://web.archive.org/web/20100824144755/http:/www.typographyforlawyers.com/?p=12). He also makes nice use of Cambria (CSS below) on the site, though this might be part of a WordPress template.

p, li {  
 font-family: Cambria, Georgia, Times New Roman, Calibri, serif;  
 font-size: 18px;  
 line-height: 25px;  
}
